body.description: Carbonless Lab Notebooks for Science Students in all disciplines! Used in Science Classrooms everywhere Our upgraded carbonless Student Lab Notebook contains 100-count or 50-count duplicate page sets, each sequentially numbered. The graph print quality is excellent on both the original and duplicate copy pages. A Table of Contents at the front of the Lab Notebook will help you keep your lab notes organized. The first page of each carbonless set is white, and the duplicate copy page is yellow - both are perforated. XanEdu Carbonless Lab Notebooks are spiral bound with a smooth high-quality coil which allows the Student Lab Notebook to easily lie flat. The Periodic Table of the Elements is printed inside the back cover for easy reference, which also acts as a fold-over divider between labs to prevent marks on the following pages.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for my needs
reviews.reviewText: I like the smoothness of the paper, but I only wish it had 5 squares/inch graph. Also, I wish that only the yellow copy paper ripped out. This book has perforations on BOTH the white and yellow, so it makes it difficult to pull out the yellow one without pulling out the white sheet a little .

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 25, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I needed this specific type of notebook for my chemistry lab in college and it was perfect. This notebook will last a really long time as well! Since I only have lab once a week, I ended up only using about 30 sheets total for the entire semester, so this notebook will last me at least three semesters!! And it came really fast through prime so that's always great too. This is worth every penny!! It is well constructed and has some really useful diagrams/information inside the cover, along with a nice periodic table on the inside.I've used it for two semesters so far and it's holding up really well! Get this for your college chem labs!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Chem Lab Notebook - Daughter loves it!!! I loved the price!
reviews.reviewText: Looks nice on all fronts. She loves the pastel periodic table. She wanted me to make sure I mentioned that the main sheets and copy sheets are separated (only held on by the spiral binding). She thinks the cover is “really cute”.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 26, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I may have failed chemistry, but this notebook didn't fail me!
reviews.reviewText: I was required to hand-write every single lab report and instructions for my college chemistry class, and this really came in handy! Way cheaper than the ones recommended from the student bookstore, and the same quality if not better. Plenty of pages (I used this for two semesters and still have plenty of room) and writing transfers neatly with little smudging, though you sometimes need to press decently hard to get clear lines if making a chart or graph.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very handy and durable
reviews.reviewText: Great carbon copy quality. I used the Hayden-McNeil lab notebook for some years and I always had issues with the copy quality and it is generally overpriced, so this is good value. To the comments that had issues with the page bleeding: this notebook only bleeds onto other copy pages if you don't place the back cover under the page you're writing on. That's just how you have to treat carbon copy pages.
